gomodel:SYNGO_1119  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099059 replaced by GO:0048787" , "Rationale: Kainate GluR7 (Grik 3) receptor\n\n8/9/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Tissue Preparation\nTwelve adult (200-250 g) and two 15-17 days old male Wistar rats were deeply anaesthetized with Sagatal (pentobarbitone sodium, 60 mg/ml i.p.) and perfused transcardially first with 0.9% saline for 1 min. This was followed for~1 5min by freshly prepared fixative containing 4% paraformaldehyde, 0.05% glutaraldehyde and 15% (v/v) saturated picric acid made up in 0.1 M phosphate buffer (PB; pH ~ 7.4). After perfusion, the brains were removed from the skull and blocks of tissue were dissected and washed in 0.1 M PB for several hours. For electron microscopic immunocytochemistry, the blocks were incubated for\ncryoprotection in 10%, followed by 20% sucrose made up in PB at 4°C overnight. To increase the penetration of the reagents, the blocks were quickly frozen using liquid nitrogen and thawed in PB. The blocks were sectioned at 70 μm thickness on a vibratome. For light microscopy, the cryoprotection and freeze-thawing steps were omitted and 60\nμm thick sections were cut." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1119" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

